            : And the Constable depos'd, That he saw the Prisoner and his Comrade drinking in an Alehouse near Billingsgate very extravagantly, whereupon he examined him how he came by the Money: That he told him, his Cousin at Stratford had given him 17 s. but he suspecting him, said he believ'd he had robb'd his Master, and secur'd him; and that he confess'd he had so done. The Prisoner deny'd the Fact at the Bar. The Jury found him <rs id="t17230828-8-verdict48" type="verdictDescription">
